{
  "text": "Late enhancement imaging was used to define infarct size in the RV and LV. Infarct size was regarded as the percentage of ventricular mass with signal intensity two standard deviations above the mean signal obtained in the remote non-infarcted myocardium (posterior wall). [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Dark areas located in the middle of a region displaying late enhancement were regarded as zones of severe microvascular obstruction and they were also considered as infarcted tissue (Figure 2) . The salvaged myocardium was regarded as the percentage of the area at risk without late enhancement 12,13 ( Figure 2) .",
